===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|矛|木|t2=tree|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s}} – wood soft enough that it can easily be cut.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*now||tender; soft}}, which has also been compared to:
* {{och-l|揉|knead, massage}}
* {{och-l|懦|pliant, cowardly}}
* {{och-l|耎}}, {{och-l|輭|pliant, soft}}
* {{och-l|肉|meat}}
* {{och-l|弱|weak}}
* {{och-l|荏|weak}}
* {{och-l|軟|soft}}
* {{och-l|孺|young and small}}
Outside of Sinitic, compare {{cog|my|နူး|t=tender}} (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).
